Sulphasalazine-induced reversible hypersensitivity pneumonitis and fatal fibrosing alveolitis: report of two cases.
 The cases of two patients with ulcerative colitis are described who developed pulmonary infiltrates during the early months of treatment with sulphasalazine.
 The first patient had a hypersensitivity pneumonitis, which was confirmed by challenge.
 Recovery was complete.
 The second patient developed a fibrosing alveolitis type reaction, with fatal outcome.
